# VivaDicta iOS Development Rules

## Swift 6.0 & Concurrency
- Use Swift 6.0 with strict concurrency enabled
- Prefer `@Observable` macro over `@StateObject` for state management
- Use actors for thread-safe access to shared resources (like WhisperContext)
- Always use `async/await` for asynchronous operations
- Avoid force unwrapping - use proper error handling

## Architecture Patterns
- Follow MVVM pattern with SwiftUI
- Keep business logic in service layers (TranscriptionService protocol)
- Use SwiftData for persistence with proper model definitions
- Maintain separation between UI (Views) and business logic (ViewModels)

## Code Style
- Use descriptive names for variables and functions
- Prefer SwiftUI over UIKit for new UI components
- Use proper access control (private, internal, public)
- Add documentation comments for public APIs

## Audio & Transcription
- Use AVAudioRecorder for audio recording
- Implement proper audio session management
- Handle transcription errors gracefully
- Support both local (Whisper.cpp) and cloud (OpenAI) services

## Testing
- Write unit tests for ViewModels and services
- Use iOS Simulator for testing (iPhone 16 Pro, latest OS)
- Test both success and error scenarios
- Mock external dependencies in tests

## Build Commands
When asked to build or test:
- Use xcodebuild with workspace: `./VivaDicta.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace`
- Target: `platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 16 Pro,OS=latest`
- Configuration: Debug for development
- Use `xcbeautify` for readable output

## File Organization
- Keep related files together (Models, Views, Services)
- Use proper folder structure: Screens/, Transcription/, Utils/
- Follow Apple's naming conventions
- Group functionality by feature, not by type

